/hook_registry.go` — How native hook names are registered and routed\\n    16→4. `cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go` — `DispatchLifecycleEvent` handler\\n    17→5. `docs/architecture/agent-guide.md` — Full implementation guide\\n    18→6. `docs/architecture/agent-integration-checklist.md` — Validation criteria\\n    19→\\n    20→**Reference implementations:** Run `Glob(\\\"cmd/entire/cli/agent/*/\\\")` to discover all existing agent packages. Pick 1-2 as reference. In each, focus on `lifecycle.go` (ParseHookEvent), `hooks.go` (HookSupport), and `types.go` (hook input structs).\\n    21→\\n    22→### Phase 2: Static Capability Checks\\n    23→\\n    24→Non-destructive CLI probing. Record PASS/WARN/FAIL for each:\\n    25→\\n    26→| Check | Command | PASS | FAIL |\\n    27→|-------|---------|------|------|\\n    28→| Binary present | `command -v $AGENT_BIN` | Found | Not found (blocker) |\\n    29→| Help output | `$AGENT_BIN --help` or `$AGENT_BIN help` | Available | No help |\\n    30→| Version info | `$AGENT_BIN --version` or `$AGENT_BIN version` | Available | N/A |\\n    31→| Hook keywords | Scan help for: hook, lifecycle, callback, event, trigger, pre-, post-, plugin, extension | Found | None found |\\n    32→| Session keywords | Scan help for: session, resume, continue, history, transcript, context | Found | None found |\\n    33→| Config directory | Check `~/.$AGENT_SLUG/`, `~/.config/$AGENT_SLUG/`, `./$AGENT_SLUG/`, `./.${AGENT_SLUG}/` | Found | None found |\\n    34→| Documentation | Web search for hook/plugin/extension docs | Found | None found |\\n    35→\\n    36→### Phase 3: Test Script Creation\\n    37→\\n    38→Based on Phase 2 findings, create an **agent-specific** test script:\\n    39→\\n    40→```\\n    41→scripts/test-$AGENT_SLUG-agent-integration.sh\\n    42→```\\n    43→\\n    44→The script is tailored to the specific agent's hook mechanism (not a generic template). Adapt the hook wiring section based on what Phase 2 discovered.\\n    45→\\n    46→**S