nd points, checkpoint validation)\\n    18→3. `cmd/entire/cli/e2e_test/agent_runner.go` — `AgentRunner` interface and existing runner implementations. Read the file to discover all current runners and the `NewAgentRunner` factory.\\n    19→4. `cmd/entire/cli/e2e_test/prompts.go` — `PromptTemplate` definitions for deterministic test prompts\\n    20→5. `cmd/entire/cli/e2e_test/assertions.go` — Shared assertion helpers (`AssertAgentSuccess`, `AssertHelloWorldProgram`, etc.)\\n    21→\\n    22→### Step 2: Read Existing E2E Scenario Tests\\n    23→\\n    24→Run `Glob(\\\"cmd/entire/cli/e2e_test/scenario_*_test.go\\\")` to find all existing scenario tests. Read each to understand the patterns:\\n    25→- How scenarios use `TestEnv` and `AgentRunner`\\n    26→- How prompts are structured for determinism\\n    27→- How assertions validate checkpoints, rewind, etc.\\n    28→\\n    29→### Step 3: Read Checkpoint Scenarios Doc\\n    30→\\n    31→Read `docs/architecture/checkpoint-scenarios.md` for the state machine and scenarios the tests should cover.\\n    32→\\n    33→### Step 4: Create AgentRunner\\n    34→\\n    35→Add a new `AgentRunner` implementation in `cmd/entire/cli/e2e_test/agent_runner.go`:\\n    36→\\n    37→**Pattern to follow** (based on existing runners):\\n    38→\\n    39→```go\\n    40→// ${AGENT_NAME}Runner implements AgentRunner for ${AGENT_NAME}.\\n    41→type ${AGENT_NAME}Runner struct {\\n    42→    Model   string\\n    43→    Timeout time.Duration\\n    44→}\\n    45→\\n    46→func New${AGENT_NAME}Runner(config AgentRunnerConfig) *${AGENT_NAME}Runner { ... }\\n    47→func (r *${AGENT_NAME}Runner) Name() string { return AgentName${AGENT_NAME} }\\n    48→func (r *${AGENT_NAME}Runner) IsAvailable() (bool, error) { ... }\\n    49→func (r *${AGENT_NAME}Runner) RunPrompt(ctx, workDir, prompt) (*AgentResult, error) { ... }\\n    50→func (r *${AGENT_NAME}Runner) RunPromptWithTools(ctx, workDir, prompt, tools) (*AgentResult, error) { ... }\\n    51→```\\n    